<subSubSection pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID="9B12D9E3-30A3-6A19-F220-3FC7DA68E1BF" authority="LeConte, 1852" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pericompsus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericompsus LeConte, 1852</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pericompsus</taxonomicName>
LeConte, 1852a: 191. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Bembidium ephippiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830 designated by LeConte (1859e: 553). Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">peri</emphasis>
(very) and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">compsos</emphasis>
(elegant), probably alluding to the nice color of the body of adults of the three species LeConte had before him [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">
New World, with about 70 species arrayed in three subgenera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Eidocompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Eidocompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (13 Neotropical species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pericompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Pericompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. (about 45 species), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erwin" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Upocompsus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="444" pageNumber="445" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Upocompsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Erwin (nine Australian species).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="444" pageNumber="445" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="444" pageNumber="445">Erwin (1974b) revised the species and provided a key for their identification.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
